analysis.title: Global Market Outlook
analysis.content: Market equilibrium persists amid latent volatility. The GMS at 52 validates a transitionary regime where credit spread compression is countered by escalating VIX premiums and stagnant net liquidity. While the fiscal-monetary nexus remains balanced, the negative momentum in equities and housing indicates a localized regime degradation. The flat OGV vector and cooling labor incentives signal an abatement of inflationary convexity, requiring liquidity preservation. [ACTION: WAIT FOR PULLBACK]
